# .gitignore — Plaintext
# Security labs drive tools (tcpdump, openssl, volatility, metasploit, prowler, …)
# that emit captures, keys, dumps and logs. Per CLAUDE.md → "Secret & artifact
# hygiene", those are referenced in the lab text, never committed.

# === Secrets — never commit ===
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*_rsa
*_dsa
*_ed25519
*.kdbx
*.token
credentials

# === Lab artifacts: captures, memory/disk images, logs ===
*.pcap
*.pcapng
*.cap
*.log
*.dmp
*.mem
*.vmem
*.raw
*.lime
*.E01
*.aff4

# === Malware samples — keep out of the repo entirely ===
samples/
*.malware

# === Python (generators / tooling) ===
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# === Static-site build output (e.g. MkDocs) ===
site/
.cache/

# === OS / editor cruft ===
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
